              <birth when="0270"/>
                  
                  
                  <floruit notBefore="0270" notAfter="0345">He was a Syriac Church Father and author of a series of 23 treaties which cover most of the theological 
                     reflections of the Persian Christian of the time. His theology is based exclusively on the Bible and is free from Greek influence, but absorbed elements of the Jewish exegetical tradition. 
                     His work was translated into Armenian, Georgian and Arabic. In Ethiopian tradition, neither the name Aphrahat nor the title of his work are known. 
                     However, at least two of his treaties are known in Gǝʿǝz: <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1275Dersan"/> and <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2041Nagarb"/>. </floruit>
